  "title": "Free-body diagrams - three ropes pulling a ring",
  "content": {
    "prompt": "<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"passage\"><div class=\"prose style:1\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a top view of a ring being pulled by three ropes in different directions in a horizontal plane. The ring is represented by a dot. A long arrow labeled 20 newtons extends horizontally to the right from the dot. A short arrow labeled 10 newtons extends upward and to the left from the dot, at an angle of 45 degrees from the vertical. A short arrow labeled 10 newtons extends downward and to the left from the dot, at an angle of 60 degrees from the vertical. A pair of axes indicates that rightward is the positive x direction, and upward is the positive y direction.\" src=\"/images/90f743c0f20ff7db241d80fee2c5842c.svg\"></div></div></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A ring is being pulled by three ropes in different directions in a horizontal plane. The magnitude and direction of each force exerted on the ring is represented in the diagram. Which of the following correctly describes the direction, if any, of the sum of the force vectors exerted on the ring within the plane shown?</p>\n",
    "answer": "i4",
    "choices": [
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The sum of the force vectors is zero.</p>",
        "value": "i1"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The sum of the force vectors is in the <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"positive x\"><math alttext=\"positive x\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mo>+</mo><mi>x</mi></math></span></span>-direction.</p>",
        "value": "i2"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The sum of the force vectors is in the <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"positive y\"><math alttext=\"positive y\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mo>+</mo><mi>y</mi></math></span></span>-direction.</p>",
        "value": "i3"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The sum of the force vectors has components in both the <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"positive x\"><math alttext=\"positive x\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mo>+</mo><mi>x</mi></math></span></span>-direction and the <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"positive y\"><math alttext=\"positive y\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mo>+</mo><mi>y</mi></math></span></span>-direction.</p>",
        "value": "i4"
      }
    ]
